---
description: AI workflow and implementation process
alwaysApply: true
---

- Always analyze existing architecture before coding.
- Never create files without justification.
- Never introduce new dependencies without explanation.
- Explain major architectural decisions.
- Implement features incrementally.
- Avoid large unreviewed changes.
- Prefer iterative development.
- Review generated code before continuing.
- Never modify unrelated files.
- Ask for clarification when requirements are ambiguous.